3229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bajoran\", \"score\": 0.9999999999363354, \"rank\": 5.579391071463871e-11, \"text\": \"Kai\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bajoran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bajoran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Very few athletes\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"all their hopes\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's almost impossible to become an athlete of Olympic standard without possessing the sort of blind self-belief and determination that crystallises gold as the primary ambition to the exclusion of all else.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic standard\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"the sort\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"blind self-belief\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"determination\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"the primary ambition\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"the exclusion\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there are a small handful of events where, for the vast majority of competitors and due to the other-worldly excellence of one other, silver is the best obtainable result.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a small handful\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"the vast majority\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"the other-worldly excellence\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"the best obtainable result\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think of anyone racing Katie Ledecky in the 1,500m or L\\u00e9on Marchandin just about anything at these Games.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 814}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1,500m\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchandin\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their golds are almost marked down before the event begins, and the rest are left to fight over the scraps.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their golds\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"the scraps\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Australia's Kurtis Marschall, his men's pole vault final was one of those events.\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1018, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999457058962, \"rank\": 4.327055490159818e-08, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those events\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He arrived already in a battle for second, as nobody at these Olympic Games is as far above the rest of the world in their chosen field as Sweden's Armand 'Mondo' Duplantis.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1240, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9999999126466756, \"rank\": 8.735230986020761e-08, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a battle\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1153}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"their chosen field\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1236}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mondo Duplantis, the best in the world by a mile.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mondo Duplantis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"a mile\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Hannah Peters) He was not just the favourite, he is by some distance the best in the world and surely the greatest pole vaulter there has ever been.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Getty Images\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"Hannah Peters\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"some distance\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"surely the greatest pole vaulter\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So long as Duplantis competes to somewhere around 80 per cent of his best ability, none of the next 11 best vaulters can come close.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Duplantis\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"somewhere around 80 per cent\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"his best ability\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1572}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"the next 11 best vaulters\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What an odd position that leaves Marschall in.\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What an odd position\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"Marschall\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ranked the fifth best in the world, he is in the presence of greatness but not realistically able to touch it.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"greatness\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And so the battle for silver unfolded.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the battle\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first step for Marschall was to clear a bar at the Olympics, something he was unable to do in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9998519990951417, \"rank\": 0.0001477967296844326, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first step\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"Marschall\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"a bar\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His \\\"no-heighter\\\" at his first Olympics stayed with him longer than he would have liked, initially dragging him down but eventually lighting a fire.\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His \\\"no-heighter\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"his first Olympics\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"a fire\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marschall cruised over his first jump of 5.50m, and shed the monkey from his back in the process.\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2176, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Marschall\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"his first jump\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"5.50m\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"the monkey\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"his back\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now he was free to compete.\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also firmly in the chase for a glorious silver were American Sam Kendricks, the Philippines' Ernest John Obiena and Greece's Emmanouil Karalis.\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998741786918, \"rank\": 1.253727942527759e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2267, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Kendricks\", \"types\": [\"